The Catalytic Effect of Cobalt Components in the Deposition Process of Active Mn
In this section, the role of cobalt components in the deposition of active Mn compound is further discussed
using cyclic voltammetry (CV) and linear sweep voltammetry (LSV) for a practical battery conﬁguration and a
home-made electrolyzer cell. Compared with the galvanostatic charging process where the time duration
in the range of 1.6–1.8 V for each charging is very short (causing a fast voltage buildup due to the full charge
of the cathode), the CV and LSV methods allow equal time at every voltage step. Therefore, well-deﬁned
